checkModloaderVersion(String, String) - Method in class de.griefed.serverpackcreator.Configuration
Depending on whether Forge or Fabric was specified as the modloader, this will call the corresponding version check to verify that the user correctly set their modloader version.
If the user specified Forge as their modloader, Configuration.isForgeVersionCorrect(String) is called and the version the user specified is checked against Forge's version manifest..
If the user specified Fabric as their modloader, Configuration.isFabricVersionCorrect(String) is called and the version the user specified is checked against Fabric's version manifest.
